---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Insurance Plans - Health, Life, Car & More | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Insurance</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Comprehensive <span class="gradient-text">Insurance Plans</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Protect your family, health, and assets with the best insurance plans from top insurers. Compare policies, get instant quotes, and buy online with exclusive discounts.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-tags"></i>
          <span>25% Discount</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i>
          <span>Instant Policy</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-building-columns"></i>
          <span>All Insurers</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">

          <!-- Overview -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Overview</span>
              <h2>Why You Need Insurance</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Insurance is one of the most important financial tools for protecting yourself and your loved ones against unforeseen events. Whether it's a medical emergency, an accident, or loss of income, the right insurance policy ensures that you're financially prepared for life's uncertainties.</p>
            <p>At TrueCred, we partner with all major insurance companies in India to bring you the best policies at the most competitive premiums. Our platform allows you to compare plans side-by-side, understand coverage in detail, and purchase policies instantly — all online with zero paperwork.</p>
            <p>From health insurance and term life plans to motor insurance and retirement policies, we offer comprehensive coverage options for every stage of life. Our dedicated insurance advisors are available to help you choose the right plan based on your specific needs, family size, and budget.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Types of Insurance -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Insurance Types</span>
              <h2>Types of Insurance Plans</h2>
            </div>

            <h3>Health Insurance</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Individual Health Insurance</strong>
                  <p>Covers medical expenses for a single person including hospitalization, pre and post-hospitalization costs, day care procedures, and ambulance charges. Sum insured options range from ₹3 Lakh to ₹1 Crore with premiums starting as low as ₹400/month.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Family Floater Plans</strong>
                  <p>A single policy that covers the entire family — self, spouse, children, and parents — under one shared sum insured. More cost-effective than individual policies for families. Premiums start from ₹800/month for a family of four with ₹5 Lakh coverage.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Critical Illness Cover</strong>
                  <p>Provides a lump-sum payout on diagnosis of specified critical illnesses like cancer, heart attack, stroke, kidney failure, and organ transplant. This amount can be used for treatment, lifestyle changes, or income replacement during recovery.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Term Life Insurance</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Pure Term Plans</strong>
                  <p>The most affordable form of life insurance that provides financial protection to your family in case of your untimely demise. Get ₹1 Crore coverage for as low as ₹500/month. No maturity benefit — pure protection at the lowest cost.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Term Plan with Return of Premium</strong>
                  <p>If you survive the policy term, all premiums paid are returned to you (without interest). Slightly higher premiums than pure term plans, but the return of premium feature makes it attractive for those who want a safety net without feeling like they've "lost" the money.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Car Insurance</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Comprehensive Car Insurance</strong>
                  <p>Covers both own damage and third-party liability. Includes protection against accidents, theft, fire, natural disasters, and vandalism. Add-ons available for zero depreciation, roadside assistance, engine protection, and return to invoice cover.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Third-Party Only (TP)</strong>
                  <p>Mandatory by law under the Motor Vehicles Act. Covers liability for injury or damage caused to a third party. Does not cover own damage. Most affordable option but offers limited protection.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Two Wheeler Insurance</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Comprehensive Bike Insurance</strong>
                  <p>Complete protection for your two-wheeler against accidents, theft, natural calamities, and third-party liability. Premiums start from just ₹600/year for comprehensive coverage. Available with add-ons like zero depreciation and personal accident cover.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Retirement Plans</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Pension & Annuity Plans</strong>
                  <p>Build a retirement corpus through regular investments during your working years and receive a guaranteed pension after retirement. Plans offer options for lump-sum withdrawal at retirement plus monthly pension. Tax benefits available under Section 80C and 80CCD.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Health Insurance Comparison Table -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Compare Plans</span>
              <h2>Health Insurance Plan Comparison</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Compare the top health insurance plans from leading insurers to find the best coverage at the most competitive premium. All plans listed below are for an individual aged 30 years with ₹5 Lakh sum insured.</p>
            <table class="rate-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Insurance Company</th>
                  <th>Sum Insured</th>
                  <th>Annual Premium</th>
                  <th>Claim Settlement Ratio</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Star Health Insurance</strong></td>
                  <td>₹5 Lakh</td>
                  <td>₹5,800/year</td>
                  <td><span style="color: #22c55e; font-weight: 600;">91.2%</span></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>HDFC Ergo Health</strong></td>
                  <td>₹5 Lakh</td>
                  <td>₹6,200/year</td>
                  <td><span style="color: #22c55e; font-weight: 600;">89.5%</span></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>ICICI Lombard</strong></td>
                  <td>₹5 Lakh</td>
                  <td>₹5,500/year</td>
                  <td><span style="color: #3b82f6; font-weight: 600;">87.8%</span></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Bajaj Allianz Health</strong></td>
                  <td>₹5 Lakh</td>
                  <td>₹5,900/year</td>
                  <td><span style="color: #3b82f6; font-weight: 600;">88.1%</span></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Niva Bupa Health</strong></td>
                  <td>₹5 Lakh</td>
                  <td>₹6,100/year</td>
                  <td><span style="color: #22c55e; font-weight: 600;">90.3%</span></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Care Health Insurance</strong></td>
                  <td>₹5 Lakh</td>
                  <td>₹5,400/year</td>
                  <td><span style="color: #3b82f6; font-weight: 600;">86.9%</span></td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p><em>*Premiums are indicative for a 30-year-old individual. Actual premiums may vary based on age, medical history, and city. Claim settlement ratios are for FY 2024-25. Last updated: April 2026.</em></p>
          </div>

          <!-- Eligibility -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Eligibility</span>
              <h2>Insurance Eligibility Criteria</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Eligibility requirements vary by insurance type. Here are the general criteria for the most common insurance products available on our platform.</p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Health Insurance</strong>
                  <p>Age: 18–65 years (entry age). Children can be covered from 91 days old under family floater plans. No medical tests required for ages 18–45 in most plans. Pre-existing diseases are covered after a waiting period of 2–4 years depending on the insurer.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Term Life Insurance</strong>
                  <p>Age: 18–65 years (entry age). Medical tests may be required for higher sum insured amounts (typically above ₹1 Crore) or for applicants above 40 years. Smokers and tobacco users pay higher premiums. Policy can continue up to age 75–85 years.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Motor Insurance</strong>
                  <p>Vehicle must be registered in India. Valid registration certificate (RC) and previous policy details required for renewal. For new vehicles, insurance must be purchased at the time of registration. No age restriction for the policyholder (must hold valid driving licence).</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Retirement Plans</strong>
                  <p>Age: 18–60 years (entry age for most plans). Minimum annual contribution ranges from ₹6,000 to ₹12,000 depending on the plan. Vesting age (when pension starts) is typically between 40–70 years. Both salaried and self-employed individuals are eligible.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- How to Buy Insurance -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">How to Buy</span>
              <h2>How to Buy Insurance on TrueCred</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Buying insurance on TrueCred is a simple, paperless process that takes just a few minutes. Follow these steps to get covered today.</p>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <h3>Select Insurance Type</h3>
                <p>Choose from Health, Term Life, Car, Two Wheeler, or Retirement insurance. Fill in basic details like age, city, and coverage amount to see personalized plans.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <h3>Compare & Choose</h3>
                <p>Compare plans from multiple insurers side-by-side. Review coverage details, premiums, claim settlement ratios, and add-on options to find the best fit.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <h3>Fill Application</h3>
                <p>Complete the application form with personal, health, and nominee details. Upload required documents like Aadhaar, PAN, and address proof digitally.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">4</div>
                <h3>Pay & Get Policy</h3>
                <p>Make a secure online payment via UPI, net banking, or credit/debit card. Your policy document is issued instantly and sent to your email within minutes.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">

          <!-- Get Quote Form -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-shield"></i> Get Free Quote</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <select required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Insurance Type</option>
                  <option value="health">Health Insurance</option>
                  <option value="term">Term Life Insurance</option>
                  <option value="car">Car Insurance</option>
                  <option value="bike">Two Wheeler Insurance</option>
                  <option value="retirement">Retirement Plans</option>
                  <option value="critical">Critical Illness Cover</option>
                  <option value="travel">Travel Insurance</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" placeholder="Your Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="number" placeholder="Your Age" min="18" max="80" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block">
                Get Quote <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
              <p class="form-disclaimer">
                <i class="fas fa-lock"></i> No spam. Instant comparison from 20+ insurers.
              </p>
            </form>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick Links -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <ul class="sidebar-links">
              <li><a href="/pages/personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Personal Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Business Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Home Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Credit Cards</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Credit Score</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/investments"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Investments</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> EMI Calculators</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Gold Loan</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQs</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Insurance</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>How much health insurance cover do I need?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>The ideal health insurance coverage depends on your age, city, family size, and lifestyle. As a general guideline, a sum insured of at least ₹5 Lakh is recommended for individuals in tier-1 cities, while ₹10 Lakh or more is advisable if you have a family. Consider factors like rising medical costs (10%–15% annual inflation), the cost of surgeries and critical treatments in your city, and whether you have employer-provided group insurance. A super top-up plan can be an affordable way to increase coverage.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What is the claim settlement ratio and why does it matter?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>The Claim Settlement Ratio (CSR) is the percentage of claims an insurance company settles against the total claims received in a financial year. A higher CSR (above 90%) indicates that the insurer is more likely to honour your claim when you need it most. While premium and coverage are important, the CSR is a critical factor to consider because the true value of insurance is realized only at the time of a claim. Always choose insurers with a CSR above 85% for peace of mind.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Are pre-existing diseases covered under health insurance?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes, pre-existing diseases (PEDs) are covered under health insurance after a waiting period, which typically ranges from 2 to 4 years depending on the insurer and the specific plan. During this waiting period, any hospitalization or treatment related to the pre-existing condition will not be covered. It is crucial to declare all pre-existing conditions honestly at the time of buying the policy, as non-disclosure can lead to claim rejection. Some insurers offer plans with reduced PED waiting periods for higher premiums.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What is the difference between term insurance and endowment plans?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Term insurance is a pure protection plan that pays the sum assured to your nominees only if you pass away during the policy term. It has no maturity benefit and offers the highest coverage at the lowest premium. Endowment plans combine insurance with savings — you get a maturity benefit if you survive the policy term, but the coverage amount is much lower for the same premium. Financial experts generally recommend buying a high-coverage term plan and investing the premium difference separately for better overall returns.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Can I buy insurance online? Is it safe?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes, buying insurance online is completely safe and is actually recommended by IRDAI (Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of India). Online policies are often 10%–25% cheaper than offline ones because insurers save on agent commissions and operational costs. The policy document issued online is legally valid and identical to offline policies. You can compare plans, read reviews, and make informed decisions at your own pace. TrueCred uses bank-grade encryption and partners only with IRDAI-licensed insurers to ensure complete safety of your transactions and personal data.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Protect What Matters Most</h2>
      <p>Compare insurance plans from 20+ top insurers. Get up to 25% discount on online purchases. Instant policy issuance.</p>
      <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
        Get Free Quote <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
